<Page x:Class="UIAtoms.WPFSamples.FormSamples.Validations.CustomValidationRuleDesc"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
      xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
      mc:Ignorable="d" 
      d:DesignHeight="300" d:DesignWidth="300"
	Title="CustomValidationRuleDesc">

    <Grid>
        <FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph>
                    UIAtoms comes packed with inbuilt validations making form building easy. 
                    However, many controls would require custom validation rules established.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    The UIAtoms CustomValidationRule demonstrated in this sample shows how custom validation rules can be provided for controls.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph>
                    The code applied can be viewed by clicking the XAML Tab. The CustomValidationRule code can be viewed by clicking the C# tab.
                </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>

    </Grid>
</Page>
